christian "chris" steinmetz (june 28, 1882 â€“ june 11, 1963) was an american basketball player. he played forward for the university of wisconsin from 1903 to 1905. he was college basketball's leading scorer in the game's first 25 years from 1895 to 1920. he became known as the "father of wisconsin basketball" and was inducted into the basketball hall of fame in 1961.